The Chronicle Farirai Machivenyika, Harare Bureau PRESIDENT Mnangagwa is today expected to meet the Zanu-PF Parliamentary caucus at the party’s headquarters in Harare, with all members of the Politburo also taking part. Zanu-PF Chief Whip Cde Pupurai Togarepi confirmed today’s meeting saying they were expecting to get guidance on legislative issues from the President. <img class="wp-image-473630 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/Cde-Pupurai-Togarepi.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/Cde-Pupurai-Togarepi.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/11/Cde-Pupurai-Togarepi-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Cde Pupurai Togarepi “Tomorrow’s meeting offers us an opportunity to interact with the President where we will get his guidance and wisdom on various issues and also an opportunity to express our gratitude for his leadership during the ninth Parliament which will be coming to an end soon,” Cde Togarepi said. He said the President was also part of the legislature, giving final approval to legislation, so it was also important that they get his views on legislative issues currently before Parliament.  Cde Togarepi said the meeting will start at 9am and MPs are expected to be at the party’s headquarters before then. <img class="wp-image-672569 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Cde-Chris-Mutsvangwa.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Cde-Chris-Mutsvangwa.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/Cde-Chris-Mutsvangwa-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zanu PF spokesperson Ambassador Christopher Mutsvangwa. Zanu-PF Secretary for Information and Publicity Cde Chris Mutsvangwa yesterday said the party Secretary for Administration Cde Obert Mpofu had invited all Politburo members to the same meeting, now a joint meeting to be addressed by the President.